course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 45 minutes
---

5 teaspoon White Wine Vinegar
2 unit Mini Cucumber
1 unit Miso Sauce Concentrate
4 ounce Shredded Carrots
½ cup Jasmine Rice
10 ounce Steelhead Trout
4 tablespoon Umami Ginger Sauce
2 tablespoon Hoisin Sauce
2 unit Scallions
1.5 ounce Sesame Dressing
Salt
Pepper
Sugar

• Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to
425 degrees.
• In a small pot, combine rice, 3⁄4 cups water (1 1⁄2 cups for
4 servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover
and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
15-18 minutes.
• Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

• Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.
• Trim and quarter cucumbers lengthwise; slice crosswise
into 1⁄2-inch-thick quarter-moons. Trim and thinly slice
scallions, separating whites from greens.
• In a medium bowl, combine cucumbers, scallion whites,
carrots, dressing, 1 tsp vinegar, and 1⁄4 tsp sugar (2 tsp
vinegar and 1⁄2 tsp sugar for 4 servings). (Be sure to measure
the vinegar—we sent more.) Season generously with salt
and pepper.
• In a small bowl, combine hoisin, miso sauce concentrate,
and umami ginger sauce; set aside.

• Pat trout* dry with paper towels; season all over with salt
and pepper.
• Place trout, skin sides down, on a baking sheet. Evenly
spread tops of trout with hoisin miso glaze. Roast on top
rack until trout is cooked through, 10-12 minutes.

• Fluff rice with a fork.
• Divide rice, trout, and cucumber carrot salad between
plates. Sprinkle everything with scallion greens and serve.

***Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.***